  "texts": [
    "Annotators in this dataset were tasked with explaining and establishing connections between visual attributes within artworks and the corresponding psychological interpretations of emotions.",
    "Within the ArtEmis dataset, annotators operate within a well-defined set of eight categorical emotion states.",
    "These emotions include four negative categories: anger, disgust, fear, and sadness, as well as four positive categories: amusement, awe, contentment, and excitement.",
    "This categorization framework helps to structure and standardize the emotional attributions provided by the annotators.",
    "The annotation process for ArtEmis was meticulous."
  ],
